<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99608090952392></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99608090952392><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/item.html?item=4805&mid=99608090952392>Designed for melee</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=79161><span id= >Antiochus</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>5 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jul 25th 1:08 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Howdy do. Having gone over some of these posts (still scratching my head from the majority of the nonsense listed here) I felt the need to put in a plug for the melee classes. I feel this item is best suited for real melees. Particularly those with lower AC items. Read as: Monks and Rogues. Rangers can do better, Warriors sure can, hybrids can too when ya get right down to it. You don't see the need for these items amongst Melee classes with lower AC/HP's until you've watched a Monk or Rogue try to tank. The haste is particularly nice for being a head slot item. Free up that back or waist for a better stat item.<br>Now I've stated before in various other posts how I feel about Bards melee'ing. May as well clear this up. In case you didn't know. Epic Rangers are now in 2nd place for front forward damage, behind Monks. So don't short them on their damage output. Bards, please, play your mana song. I beg of you, don't get in my way when I'm trying to lay down some smack because you sincerely believe you outdamage Warriors. You don't take the beating, you can't dish the damage. You're not a Bard because you're a l33t damage d00d. You're a Bard because you can double as a poor man's enchanter, assist greatly with group resists, hastes, regen etc.. don't let your damage dealing dillusions get in the way of your job or in the way of my fists for that matter. You're useful but you're no meatshield and you have no taunt button so don't sell my Warrior partners short either. Yes, groups may need you, but it's wrongful for a Bard to feel that they're a more worthy party member of the damage variety than a Warrior or Ranger. And Bards CERTAINLY have better Class based gear available for them than this.<br><br>There, I feel better. Now back to the subject at hand. This is a melee class item in my humble opinion. No doubt. I say Monks and Rogues should have first shot at it. We don't have nearly as many alternatives as some would assume. I have a Tranix Crown, Frog Crown, Kobold Jester's Crown and even my cute little STR booster, Grandmaster's Headband. But I'd jump all over this in a heartbeat. But real priority, Ebony Headband!  /drool  On with the show and good day.<br>&nbsp;<br>Antiochus Oogly<br>55 Master (and growing!)<br>Mithaniel Marr</td></tr>
